Subject: in_dxf: rational HATCH spline read knots as weights (index overrun)

A rational spline boundary edge stores num_knots knot values (DXF code 40)
BEFORE the per-control-point weights (also code 40). The importer decided
knot-vs-weight purely on `l >= 0 && is_rational`, so every knot after the
first was routed to the weight branch: it overwrote control_points[0].weight,
never advanced the knot index, and left `l` stuck at 0 so the knot-complete
reset never fired. The control points then indexed from the wrong base and
ran past num_control_points ("wrong l N control_points index"), aborting the
whole DXF import (READ ERROR 0x800) -- e.g. Planos Constructivos, a spline
with num_knots=18 / num_control_points=14.

Track a knots_left counter (set at code 95, decremented per knot) and only
treat code 40 as a weight once the knots are consumed. Planos now imports
and round-trips clean through ODA; 254 unit tests green.

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/in_dxf.c
+++ b/src/in_dxf.c
@@ add_HATCH locals
   int l = -1;
+  int knots_left = 0; // spline knots pending; they precede rational weights
@@ code 95 num_knots
   o->paths[j].segs[k].num_knots = pair->value.l;
+  knots_left = (int)pair->value.l;
@@ code 40 case 4 SPLINE
-  if (l >= 0 && o->paths[j].segs[k].is_rational)
+  if (knots_left <= 0 && l >= 0 && o->paths[j].segs[k].is_rational)
     { ...weight... }
   else
-    { l++; CHK_knots; knots[l] = val; ... }
+    { l++; CHK_knots; knots[l] = val; knots_left--; ... }
